The 29-year-old man accused of a triple murder and rape in Sobantu in KwaZulu-Natal remains in police custody. eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli was in court and filed this report. Courtesy of #DStv403 SOBANTU - Police in KwaZulu Natal have confirmed that the suspect accused of murdering three family members in Sobantu township previously faced a murder charge. Njabulo Ndlovu made a brief appearance at the Pietermaritzburg magistrate's court where he opted to abandon his bail. READ:Â Sobantu triple murder | Family members want suspect kept in prison He is accused of murdering and raping 65-year-old Zanele Ndlela, her 46-year-old daughter Smangele and eight-year-old granddaughter Zenande. Angry community members protested outside the court, calling for an end to Gender-Based Violence.